Former PIC Boss Dan Matjila will be on the stand for the third week this week. He will undergo a cross examination as well as continue to explain his involvement in over 10 controversial investments. JOHANNESBURG - Former PIC Boss Dan Matjila is expected to return to the PIC inquiry on Monday. He will undergo cross-examination as well as continue to explain his involvement in over 10 controversial investments. READ: I'm not corrupt, says Matjila Matjila is expected to touch on investments such as DayBreak Farm, Erin Energy and Echo Bank.